# -*- changelog-version: 2.0 -*-
# -*- release-nodes: 3 -*-
# -*- release-file: changelog-releases.yaml -*-
#
# Behaviour-focused changelog for Quartermaster. Every entry describes a change
# an MCP client or a web-UI user can observe; pure chore/build/refactor commits
# are intentionally omitted. This file is the single source of truth: the root
# CHANGELOG.md (Markdown) and server/app/assets/text/changelog.json (served to
# the web UI) are both rendered from it with `task changelog` (clproc).
#
# Each subject is prefixed with an audience marker the web UI turns into a
# filterable chip: [MCP] (tool behaviour), [UI] (web UI), [API] (REST), or
# [Ops] (operation/deployment). The `highlight` column ("x") marks the most
# important MCP-behaviour milestones.
#
# Columns:
#   version ; type ; subject ; issue_ids ; internal ; highlight ; detail
# type is a "Keep a Changelog" value (added/changed/security/fixed/support/...).
#
# version     ; type     ; subject                                                                          ; issues ; i ; h ; detail
#---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Unreleased (on main, ahead of the newest tag) -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- 2026.7.13 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.7.13a3   ; changed  ; [MCP] Agents can now run and explain the catalog evaluation for kit authors       ;        ;   ;   ; The server instructions point kit authors at the `catalog_evaluation` prompt, and that runbook now carries a full interpretation guide — which findings fail a case versus which are advisory, the confirmed-spurious and runaway-trait nuance, a triage order, and a per-finding fix map. A coding agent with Quartermaster registered can discover the runbook, run the evaluation locally against the author's own kit folder, and explain the report with concrete manifest fixes rather than only naming sections.
2026.7.13a3   ; changed  ; [Ops] Embedding-model warmup is announced instead of looking like a hang          ;        ;   ;   ; The server logs a "warming embedding model at startup" line before the blocking startup warmup (paired with the existing completion line), and the evaluation CLI prints a one-time model-load notice on non-terminal runs. Neither the container boot nor a piped eval run now goes silent while the model loads.
2026.7.13a2   ; changed  ; [Ops] Progress feedback and resource guidance for the catalog-evaluation CLI      ;        ;   ;   ; `python -m app.eval` now shows a live progress bar while it runs and a prettified summary report at the end when run in a terminal (piped output stays plain text). The documented container command caps the resource-heavy run with `--cpus 2 --memory 2g`, which you can drop for full power.
2026.7.13a1   ; added    ; [MCP] Kit-catalog resolution evaluation for authors                               ;        ;   ; x ; Kit authors can measure how well a catalog resolves — per-kit coverage, false-exclusions (a kit silently dropped when an over-inferred trait matches its `excludes`), and cross-kit interference — over any kit folder, including not-yet-deployed kits in any domain. Exposed through the `evaluate_catalog` MCP tool and the domain-agnostic `catalog_evaluation` prompt.
2026.7.13a1   ; added    ; [API] Asynchronous catalog-evaluation endpoint                                    ;        ;   ;   ; `POST /api/eval/resolution` starts an evaluation run and `GET /api/eval/resolution/{id}` polls it for the scored report: failing cases, false-exclusions, cross-kit interference, and trait contamination.

# --- 2026.7.12 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.7.12a3   ; fixed    ; [MCP] A broken kit no longer takes down the whole catalog                         ;        ;   ; x ; A kit whose instructions index is missing or malformed is now isolated and excluded from selection instead of aborting the entire catalog load, so `list_kits`/`resolve_kits` keep serving every healthy kit.
2026.7.12a3   ; added    ; [UI] Broken kits surfaced in the kit list                                         ;        ;   ;   ; The kit list flags a malformed kit with an alert row and its load error (and no detail link) so it can be found and fixed.
2026.7.12a3   ; fixed    ; [UI] Bare `/docs` reaches the documentation site                                  ;        ;   ;   ; Visiting `/docs` now redirects to the rendered docs index instead of returning the app shell, and a "Docs" link was added to the top navigation.
2026.7.12a1   ; added    ; [UI] Public pre-login landing page                                               ;        ;   ;   ; A public landing page now greets visitors before sign-in, so the product is legible without authenticating first.
2026.7.12a1   ; changed  ; [UI] Tactical navy/brass redesign with light and dark theming                    ;        ;   ;   ; The web UI was restyled with a coherent navy/brass palette across both the light and dark Vuetify themes.
2026.7.12a1   ; added    ; [MCP] Per-repo kit version pinning via a repo-side `.quartermaster.toml`          ;        ;   ; x ; A repository can pin the kit version it expects in a `.quartermaster.toml`. Then `resolve_kits`/`get_kit` honour that pin so a repo stays on a known kit revision.

# --- 2026.7.4 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.7.4a1    ; added    ; [MCP] MCP prompt templates bundled as package markdown                           ;        ;   ;   ; The canned MCP prompts are now maintained as bundled markdown templates rather than inline strings, so the prompt text delivered to clients is easier to review and extend.

# --- 2026.7.3 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.7.3a3    ; added    ; [MCP] Harness-enforced `resolve_kits` re-run triggers                            ;        ;   ; x ; The MCP `instructions` string and the `resolve_kits` docstring now carry an explicit re-run trigger list: call it again on a change/plan request, when starting a new subsystem, on a direction shift, and after a context compaction.
2026.7.3a3    ; added    ; [UI] Integrate page ships copy-pasteable agent enforcement hooks                 ;        ;   ;   ; The Integrate page gained a harness-enforcement section with ready-to-paste Claude Code hooks (and guidance for opencode, Cursor, Cline, Windsurf and rules-only agents) that keep `resolve_kits` firing throughout a session.
2026.7.3a2    ; added    ; [MCP] App tokens accepted as `Authorization: Bearer` on the MCP mount            ;        ;   ; x ; Long-lived app tokens now work as bearer credentials on the MCP mount and REST API, giving clients that cannot refresh OAuth (notably opencode) a stable credential.
2026.7.3a2    ; fixed    ; [UI] Metrics time-series render on a real UTC time axis                          ;        ;   ;   ; The metrics dashboard now plots its series against an actual UTC time axis instead of evenly-spaced buckets.

# --- 2026.7.2 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.7.2a3    ; added    ; [MCP] Guided auto-evolution: catalog-recall gap detection                        ;        ;   ; x ; When trait inference finds nothing, `resolve_kits` now runs a fuzzy recall pass and reports a genuine catalog gap. New tools `check_existing_gap_issue` and `request_clarification_or_addition` let an agent surface the gap to maintainers.
2026.7.2a3    ; added    ; [MCP] Per-user memory tools `get_my_memory` / `reset_my_memory`                  ;        ;   ;   ; A bounded, per-caller familiarity profile derived from your own resolve history nudges kit ranking (never overriding a real trait match). It is viewable and resettable over the MCP.
2026.7.2a1    ; changed  ; [UI] Catalog-growth metrics chart gains a domain selector                       ;        ;   ;   ; The catalog-growth chart can now be filtered by domain.

# --- 2026.7.1 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.7.1a4    ; added    ; [MCP] Owner-only private kits over the MCP                                       ;        ;   ; x ; Any authenticated user can author private kits that are visible only to them across `list_kits`, `select_kits`, `resolve_kits` and `get_kit`. Non-owner reads return 404 and private kits never poison the shared trait vocabulary.
2026.7.1a4    ; added    ; [API] Editor/consumer roles with `GET /api/me` and `/api/roles`                 ;        ;   ;   ; Two roles are introduced — editor (manages the shared catalog and grants roles) and consumer (read-only default) — with new endpoints to read your role and manage the subject-to-role mapping.
2026.7.1a4    ; security ; [Security] Kit mutations now require the editor role (HTTP 403 for consumers)     ;        ;   ;   ; Every kit-writing REST route and WebDAV write method is gated to editors (default-deny). Breaking for existing deployments: set QM_INITIAL_EDITORS to keep editing.
2026.7.1a4    ; added    ; [UI] Users admin screen and Private kits screen                                  ;        ;   ;   ; The web UI gained a Users admin screen (role management) and a Private screen for authoring owner-only kits. Edit controls are hidden for consumers.
2026.7.1a3    ; added    ; [UI] Metrics dashboard 1h/1d granularity toggle                                  ;        ;   ;   ; An Hourly/Daily switch re-buckets the token and catalog-growth charts. `GET /api/metrics/overview` gained a `granularity` parameter.
2026.7.1a2    ; changed  ; [UI] Kit-layer chip and centred app-bar navigation                               ;        ;   ;   ; The active kit layer is shown as a chip and the top navigation was centred.

# --- 2026.6.30 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.6.30a1   ; changed  ; [MCP] `resolve_kits` aligned with MCP prompts, sampling and elicitation           ;        ;   ; x ; Trait inference now prefers the connecting client's own LLM via MCP sampling (degrading to embeddings, then a lexical floor) and can elicit a clarification. A diagnostic mode reports which engine produced the result.
2026.6.30a1   ; added    ; [MCP] Onboarding prompts                                                         ;        ;   ;   ; New canned MCP prompts guide first-time integration.
2026.6.30a2   ; added    ; [UI] Always-on local metrics dashboard (independent of OpenTelemetry)            ;        ;   ;   ; A built-in metrics dashboard now works without any external OTEL collector.

# --- 2026.6.26 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.6.26a4   ; added    ; [MCP] `resolve_kits` one-shot discovery tool                                     ;        ;   ; x ; Free-text task in, ranked kits out with each kit's always_load sections already inlined. Server-side trait inference collapses the whole list/select/explain/outline/get discovery loop into a single call.
2026.6.26a4   ; changed  ; [MCP] Discovery surfaces now lead with `resolve_kits`                            ;        ;   ;   ; The tool docstrings and server instructions steer clients to `resolve_kits` as the default discovery entry point.
2026.6.26a1   ; added    ; [MCP] Tool-call audit logging                                                    ;        ;   ;   ; Every MCP tool call is now audit-logged on the server.
2026.6.26a3   ; added    ; [UI] Dark Vuetify theme alongside the existing light theme                       ;        ;   ;   ; The web UI ships both a light and a dark theme.
2026.6.26a3   ; changed  ; [API] POST creates return a Location header, DELETE returns 204 No Content        ;        ;   ;   ; Resource-creating POSTs now return a Location header. DELETE of a kit version or section returns 204 No Content with no body (breaking for clients that read the old 200 payload).
2026.6.26a3   ; changed  ; [Ops] All server environment variables are now prefixed with `QM_`               ;        ;   ;   ; Configuration is namespaced (e.g. KEYCLOAK_URL becomes QM_KEYCLOAK_URL, KITS_ROOT becomes QM_KITS_ROOT). Breaking: rename every server variable to the QM_ form. VITE_* build variables are unchanged.
2026.6.26a3   ; added    ; [Ops] Health probes `/livez`, `/readyz`, `/healthz` and hardening middleware     ;        ;   ;   ; Dedicated liveness/readiness probes, a per-request correlation id, standard security headers, an X-Quartermaster-Version header, and opt-in rate limiting on registration/token endpoints.
2026.6.26a3   ; added    ; [UI] Build-identity strip: source-repository link and commit chip                ;        ;   ;   ; The web UI can show a link to the source repository plus a commit chip and identicon, each hidden when its build variable is absent.

# --- 2026.6.25 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2026.6.25a3   ; added    ; [UI] opencode integration setup on the Integrate page                            ;        ;   ;   ; The Integrate page documents how to connect the opencode client.
2026.6.25a2   ; added    ; [Ops] Configurable TLS verification for Keycloak validation                      ;        ;   ;   ; TLS verification against the Keycloak realm can be configured for self-hosted / proxied setups.

# --- 0.1.0 — Initial public release -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
0.1.0         ; added    ; [MCP] Initial kit toolset: list_kits, get_kit_outline, get_kit, list_kit_versions, compare_kit_versions ; ; ; ; First public release of the kit MCP tools for loading versioned instruction kits on demand.
0.1.0         ; added    ; [MCP] V2 trait-based selector: list_available_traits, select_kits, explain_kit_candidate ; ; ; ; Kits are ranked against a project's traits (languages/frameworks/capabilities/contexts) with requires/excludes/priority.
0.1.0         ; added    ; [UI] Vue 3 + Vuetify web UI for kit management and MCP integration               ;        ;   ;   ; A single-page web UI for browsing/managing kits and setting up MCP integration.
0.1.0         ; support  ; [Ops] Keycloak-gated auth, REST admin API and embedded WebDAV authoring          ;        ;   ;   ; Auth terminates in the application (Keycloak JWTs), with a REST admin API and a WebDAV authoring endpoint. The kit catalog is supplied at runtime and never bundled.

